{"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"platforms":["Linux"],"tokens":[{"text":"final","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"InvertedPendulum","kind":"identifier"}],"languages":["swift"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"kind":"content","content":[{"level":3,"type":"heading","text":"Description","anchor":"Description"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This environment is the cartpole environment based on the work done by"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Barto, Sutton, and Anderson in "},{"identifier":"https:\/\/ieeexplore.ieee.org\/document\/6313077","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":","},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"just like in the classic environments but now powered by the Mujoco physics simulator -"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"allowing for more complex experiments (such as varying the effects of gravity)."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"This environment involves a cart that can moved linearly, with a pole fixed on it"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"at one end and having another end free. The cart can be pushed left or right, and the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"goal is to balance the pole on the top of the cart by applying forces on the cart."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"level":3,"type":"heading","text":"Action Space","anchor":"Action-Space"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The agent take a 1-element vector for actions."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"The action space is a continuous "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"(action)"},{"type":"text","text":" in "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"[-3, 3]"},{"type":"text","text":", where "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"action"},{"type":"text","text":" represents"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the numerical force applied to the cart (with magnitude representing the amount of"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"force and sign representing the direction)"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"table","header":"row","rows":[[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Num"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Action","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Control Min","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Control Max"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Name (in corresponding XML file)"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Joint"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Unit"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"0","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Force applied on the cart","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"-3","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"3","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"slider","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"slide"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Force (N)","type":"text"}]}]]]},{"level":3,"type":"heading","text":"Observation Space","anchor":"Observation-Space"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The state space consists of positional values of different body parts of"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the pendulum system, followed by the velocities of those individual parts (their derivatives)"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"with all the positions ordered before all the velocities."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"The observation is a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ndarray"},{"type":"text","text":" with shape "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"(4,)"},{"type":"text","text":" where the elements correspond to the following:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"table","header":"row","rows":[[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Num","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Observation","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Min","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Max"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Name (in corresponding XML file)"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Joint"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Unit","type":"text"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"0","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"position of the cart along the linear surface","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"-Inf","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Inf"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"slider","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"slide","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"position (m)","type":"text"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"1"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"vertical angle of the pole on the cart","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"-Inf"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Inf"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"hinge"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"hinge"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"angle (rad)"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"2","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"linear velocity of the cart"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"-Inf","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Inf","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"slider","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"slide","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"velocity (m\/s)"}]}]],[[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"3"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"angular velocity of the pole on the cart"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"-Inf","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Inf","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"hinge","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"hinge"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"anglular velocity (rad\/s)","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]]]},{"level":3,"type":"heading","text":"Rewards","anchor":"Rewards"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The goal is to make the inverted pendulum stand upright (within a certain angle limit)"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"as long as possible - as such a reward of +1 is awarded for each timestep that"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the pole is upright."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"level":3,"type":"heading","text":"Starting State","anchor":"Starting-State"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"All observations start in state","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"(0.0, 0.0, 0.0, 0.0) with a uniform noise in the range","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"of [-0.01, 0.01] added to the values for stochasticity.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"level":3,"type":"heading","text":"Episode End","anchor":"Episode-End"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The episode ends when any of the following happens:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"orderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Truncation: The episode duration reaches 1000 timesteps."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Termination: Any of the state space values is no longer finite.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Termination: The absolutely value of the vertical angle between the pole and the cart is greater than 0.2 radian.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"level":3,"type":"heading","text":"Arguments","anchor":"Arguments"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"No additional arguments are currently supported."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["env = gym.make('InvertedPendulum-v4')"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":null},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"There is no v3 for InvertedPendulum, unlike the robot environments where a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"v3 and beyond take gym.make kwargs such as xml_file, ctrl_cost_weight, reset_noise_scale etc.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"level":3,"type":"heading","text":"Version History","anchor":"Version-History"},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"v4: all mujoco environments now use the mujoco bindings in mujoco>=2.1.3","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"v3: support for gym.make kwargs such as xml_file, ctrl_cost_weight, reset_noise_scale etc. rgb rendering comes from tracking camera (so agent does not run away from screen)","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"v2: All continuous control environments now use mujoco_py >= 1.50"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"v1: max_time_steps raised to 1000 for robot based tasks (including inverted pendulum)","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"v0: Initial versions release (1.0.0)","type":"text"}]}]}]}]}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/org.liuliu.s4nnc\/documentation\/Gym\/InvertedPendulum","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"sections":[],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/gym\/invertedpendulum"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"kind":"symbol","topicSections":[{"identi